    <a href="/reading/prose-writing/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to prose writing</a>

    <h1>Style: Lessons in Clarity and Grace</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Joseph Williams &middot; 1981 &middot; Copyrighted &mdash; cite only, no excerpts</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Williams explains why sentences feel clear or muddy, and gives you the structural analysis to fix them. Two principles do most of the work. First: put old information before new (the given-new contract). Second: use verbs, not nominalizations. &ldquo;The investigation of the problem&rdquo; is muddy. &ldquo;We investigated the problem&rdquo; is clear. Information flows from known to unknown. Violate the flow and the reader stalls.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Given-new contract chain + nominalization transformation -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 280" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">

        <!-- Title: Given-New Contract -->
        <text x="260" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.6">the given-new contract</text>

        <!-- Sentence 1 -->
        <rect x="60" y="35" width="120" height="30" rx="3" fill="#a1a1aa" fill-opacity="0.08" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="90" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.35">given</text>
        <line x1="120" y1="38" x2="120" y2="62" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.8" stroke-opacity="0.2"/>
        <rect x="120" y="35" width="120" height="30" rx="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.08" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="180" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.7">NEW</text>
        <text x="30" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.25">S1</text>

        <!-- Arrow from S1 NEW to S2 given -->
        <path d="M 240 55 C 270 55, 270 105, 240 105" fill="none" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <line x1="240" y1="105" x2="180" y2="105" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <polygon points="183,102 175,105 183,108" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.3"/>

        <!-- Sentence 2 -->
        <rect x="60" y="90" width="120" height="30" rx="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.06" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.2"/>
